ACT 1. SCENE V.

Simo, aster parting with Davus, goes to the forum, where, meeting with Pamphilus, he pretends, according to the scheme laid open to Sosia, that he must that day prepare for his marriage with Chremes' daughter. Pamphilus, disconcerted by a proposal so sudden and unex— pected‚ deliberates here with himself what he is to do. Mysis is intro- duced to turn the scale. At her appearance, all his former soft and tendor sentiments in respect of Glycerium revive, and he is confirmed in the resolution of adhering to her in spite of all opposition.
